<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hive1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hive,</orth> subst. 1) a receptacle for bees: <bibl n="shak. luc 839" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 839</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 839" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 839</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 2, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.78" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 81</bibl>.<lb />2) a swarm of bees: <cit><quote>an angry h. of bees,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.125" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 125</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) a kind of bonnet resembling a hive: <cit><quote>upon her head a platted h. of straw,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 8" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 8</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>